<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-DoxMFFYAuQwzBS4kenx3Sw" name=",_l8v9MJ5SEeCHFd5_MqJHKQ" guid="-DoxMFFYAuQwzBS4kenx3Sw" changeDate="2011-07-01T02:36:53.644-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The hardware safety requirements specification is derived from the the technical safety requirements allocated to the&#xD;
    particular piece of HW and&amp;nbsp;shall contain each HW requirement that relates to safety.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    This includes hardware safety requirements of safety mechanisms:-&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            To control internal failures of the HW and their attributes.&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            To make the element under consideration fault tolerant to external failures that might affect the element, with&#xD;
            their attributes.&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            To comply with the safety requirements of other elements.&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            To detect and signal internal and external failures.&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    The criteria for qualification and testing of the hardware item or elements is specified in ISO 26262 volume 8, clause 13&#xD;
    and should comply with ISO 26262, volume 5 clause 10.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For further details of example of the types of requirements that the above covers, the user is directed to ISO 26262&#xD;
    volume 5, clause 6.4.2.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
